* Unless the matter is confidential, it is usually better to leave a message on the user's discussion page.
* Users may have a dedicated email address for Wikibooks correspondence that is not regularly checked.
* It is usually a good idea to let the user know on their discussion page that you have sent them an email.
* If you are referring to a specific Wikibooks page, remember to include its exact title.
* The message is sent as plain text: wiki markup (such as <tt><nowiki>[[links]]</nowiki></tt>) will not work.

