{{edit filter navigation}}
Welcome to the Edit Filter management interface. Using the Edit Filter, authorized users can configure a wide range of tests which may help identify and prevent potentially harmful edits and other activities before they are added to the wiki, and the automatic actions to be taken.

Guidelines for creating and editing filters:
* ''PLEASE be careful''. This is potent stuff. If you can, always test your filters with no actions enabled first.
* The ''examine'' and ''test'' interfaces are '''awesome''' for learning the ropes. They let you look at specific edits and filters in detail, without real-world consequences.
* Keep an eye on the log.

{{Warning|'''Please be careful when creating or modifying a filter.''' Even a single typo can potentially disrupt the editing of legitimate contributors.  It is strongly recommended that you test your filters first before you enable any actions. If you are not sure about something, please  [[Wikibooks:Reading room/Technical Assistance|ask for help]].
}}

